   <text>
      <body>
         <div>
            <head>18.6.1880 Freitag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49056">Ems</placeName> 18 June 1880 Sun rises 3,44, sets
      8,17</p>
            <p>
               <persName key="176">Papa</persName> and I this morning go up the Malberg without taking the
     way up but by climbing straight up the mountain, the heat is torrid and we are soon as if
     we had been dipped in a bath; from the tower which is situated on the top of the mountain
     the vew is lovely on the first plan <placeName key="49056">Ems</placeName>, the Lahn and
     the Concordiathurm on which we were yesterday, on the
     second the silverworks and mines, Chemna <note type="reg">
                  <placeName key="80485">Kemmenau</placeName>
               </note>, and the road to <placeName key="49058">Nassau</placeName>
     and lost in the far horizont the Rheinthal, castel Stolzenfels, a
     ruin and the Taunus itself. This afternoon there has been a storm with thunder, lightening
     rain and every thing to complete it as if the weather before setting to &#x201e;Kaiserwetter&#x201c;
     which means emperorsweather because the <persName key="10133">emperor</persName> allways
     has fine weather when he arrives; wanted to have one more good rage. </p>
         </div>
